TEXT(beginproblem());
$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 1;
Context("Numeric");
$a=random(2,4,1);
$ans1=random(3,5,1);
$b=$a*$ans1; 
$c1=random(4,8,2);
$c2=random(5,7,2);
Context("Fraction");
$c=Compute("$c1/$c2");
$d1=random(3,7,2);
$d=Compute("$d1/4");
$ans2=$d/$c;
Context("Numeric");
$e=random(5,9,2)/20;
$f=random(11,19,2)/40;

$ans3=$f/$e;

BEGIN_TEXT
In each of the following equations, solve to find the value of x.
$PAR
a)  If \($a x= $b\) then \(x= \) \{ans_rule(3)\}
$PAR
b)  If \( \frac{$c1}{$c2} x= \frac{$d1}{4}\) then \(x= \) \{ans_rule(3)\}
$PAR
c)  If \($e x= $f\) then \(x= \) \{ans_rule(3)\}

END_TEXT
	ANS(Real($ans1)->cmp);
	ANS($ans2->cmp);
	ANS(Real($ans3)->cmp);
BEGIN_SOLUTION
$PAR Solution $PAR
a)  \($a x= $b\).  Divide both sides b $a.$PAR
The others are solved in the same way. Remember, if you have to divide by a fraction you must invert and multiply.
END_SOLUTION


